26    /**
27    * <p>A compiler pass combining multiple {@link Callback}
28    * and {@link ScopedCallback} objects. This pass can be used to separate
29    * logically different verifications without incurring any additional traversal
30    * and CFG generation costs.</p>
31    *
32    * <p>Due to this compiler pass' nature, none of the callbacks may mutate
33    * the parse tree.</p>
34    *
35    * <p>TODO(user):
36    * This combined pass is currently limited in the type of callbacks it can
37    * combine due to the difficulty of handling NodeTraversal's methods that
38    * initiate more recursion (e.g., {@link NodeTraversal#traverse(Node)} and
39    * {@link NodeTraversal#traverseInnerNode(Node, Node, Scope)}). The
40    * {@link NodeTraversal} object passed to the individual callbacks should
41    * be instrumented to emulate the correct behavior. For instance,
42    * one could create a {@link NodeTraversal} whose
43    * {@link NodeTraversal#traverseInnerNode(Node, Node, Scope)} ties
44    * back into this compiler pass to give it context about what combined
45    * passes are doing.</p>
46    *
47    */
